The Chronicle DStv’s biggest night, the DStv Mzansi Viewer’s Choice Awards (DMVCA) which celebrates the best in television, movies, music and media personalities in South Africa occurred on Saturday evening on the back of a two-year hiatus due to Covid-19. <img class="wp-image-621592 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-129.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-129.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-129-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Abdul Khoza Hosted at Sun Arena Times Square in Tshwane, the awards had the biggest stars in South Africa dressed in their best black-tie attire. Big Brother Mzansi host Lawrence Maleka played host of the event that was broadcast live on Mzansi Magic (DStv channel 161). Maleka had a good night as he was voted Favourite TV presenter. <img class="wp-image-621589 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-127.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-127.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-127-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Kwenzo Ngcobo The break-out star of Showmax The Wife, Kwenzo Ngcobo (Nqoba) was voted Favourite Rising Star. Connie Ferguson walked away with Favourite Personality and dedicated her award to her late husband Shona Ferguson. <img class="wp-image-621586 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-128.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-128.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-128-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Connie Ferguson Sannah Mchunu’s comic timing and display of sheer emotion on-screen, while shaking up the trends on social media has undeniably made her one of Mzansi’s most loved actresses and this saw her emerge the DMVCA favourite actress. The DMVCAs seek to honour the top achievers who have made their mark over the past two years in television, radio, music, sports and comedy. The entire award show was voted by the public and voting closed on June 11, 2022. Artistes who performed included Sun EL Musician, Tuks Senganga, Nomfundo Moh, Kamo Mphela, Boohle and Pabi Cooper. There were also appearances by Boity, Somizi and Thando Thabethe.  Below is a full list of DStv Mzansi Viewers Choice Awards winners: Favourite Song Makhadzi ft Prince Benza – Ghanama Favourite TV Presenter Lawrence Maleka Favourite Comedian Skhumba Hlophe Favourite Rising Star Kwenzo Ngcobo Favourite Radio Personality Selbeyonce Favourite Actor Abdul Khoza Favourite Actress Sannah Mchunu Favourite Music Artist/Group Makhadzi Favourite DJ Shimza Favourite Sports Personality: Rassie Erasmsus Favourite Personality Connie Ferguson — Sowetan/SundayWorld